cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it deals with malware detection and classification, which is a growing problem in the field of cybersecurity. The use of machine learning also suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The approach presented in the paper also involves automated feature discovery, which could place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the use of opcode features suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
